<h2>Markers</h2>

<p class="medium-7 large-5">
  <a href="https://developers.google.com/maps/documentation/javascript/3.exp/reference#MarkerOptions" target="_blank">Goolge Map Markers</a> allow you to add an indicator to a specific coordinate. Use Google's default marker, or apply your own custom marker.  Markers support a range of user interactions and are draggable as well.  Also if you want to add context or information about a location you can use the marker's <span class="gmaps-inline-code">infoWindow</span> property.
</p>

<div class="grid-block -spb">
  <div class="grid-content small-12 medium-3 -smb">
    <small class="-db">Latitude</small>
    {{marker.lat}}
  </div>

  <div class="grid-content small-12 medium-3 -smb">
    <small class="-db">Longitude</small>
    {{marker.lng}}
  </div>

  <div class="grid-content small-12 medium-3 -smb">
    <small class="-db">Is Dragging</small>
    {{isMarkerDragging}}
  </div>

  <div class="grid-content small-12 medium-3 -smb">
    <small class="-db">Custom Icon</small>
    <input type="checkbox" value=isCustomIcon {{action "toggleCustomMarker" on="change"}}>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="grid-content -np -lmb">
  {{g-maps class="gmaps-docs-map" lat=lat lng=lng zoom=zoom markers=markers}}
</div>

